latestPosts.caption:
Happy 10th Birthday to my sweet boy, Fox 🖤🐾

A whole decade with you—how did I get so lucky?

I brought you home in July 2015, just an 8 week old boy, with your wobbly little legs and smooshy face, and from that moment on, you’ve been my entire heart. I had only been in California for 10 months, still finding my place, and then you showed up—my silky soulmate.

You’ve seen me through so many chapters: heartbreaks and new love, career changes, growth, joy, grief, and everything in between. You’ve been my little shadow.

You go by many names in this house:
Fox, Silk, Silky, Silkman, Silk the Shocker, Silky Johnston, Silky MaGillacuddy, Monkey Man, Bob, Bobby, Bobby Hill, Bobby Digital, Bobert, Bert, Bubbie, Bubz, Fump, Kook, Kookie, Coconut, Nuge, and Ted Nugent (?!?)—but no matter the weird nickname, you’ve always been my best boy.

Thank you for every walk, every cuddle, every little snort. You’ve made my life so full.

Here’s to more tail wags, morning walks, and silky snuggles. I love you beyond words, Bobby Digital. 💫🖤
